From 124edceaaf2a93f6a3b833e767ed4874f0b3495a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: charlesmamane26-sketch <charlesmamane1826@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:13:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 06/11] fix(cdp): gate file:// on interception path, validate
 WS Origin/Host, safe logs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CDP-01/SSRF-05: the file:// gate lived only in do_navigate, but a normal Puppeteer/Playwright attach routes every Page.navigate through process_with_interception, which navigated with no gate — any CDP client could read arbitrary local files by default. Enforce the gate at that entry too.

CDP-02: the WebSocket handshake did no Origin/Host validation, so a web page in the victim's browser could new WebSocket('ws://127.0.0.1:9222/...') and drive the engine. Inspect the handshake: reject non-allowlisted Origins (OBSCURA_CDP_ALLOWED_ORIGINS) and pin Host to loopback. CDP-04: char-boundary-safe log truncation (a byte slice panicked the task on multi-byte input).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

